item.title: Are eggs good for senior citizens?
item.description: Eggs are an inexpensive, widely available and easily digestible source of high-quality protein and contain a significant proportion of leucine, an amino acid that is important for muscle synthesis, as well as many other nutrients of significance for older people, including vitamin D and omega-3 fatty acids. How many eggs a week should a senior eat? The American Heart Association recommends up to one egg a day for most people, fewer for people with high blood cholesterol, especially those with diabetes or who are at risk for heart failure, and up to two eggs a day for older people with normal cholesterol levels and who eat a healthy diet.

item.description: Question: How do I prevent sleep wrinkles? Because the forces from contact with the pillow that cause the skin to be stretched, pushed and pulled are mechanical, muscle immobilizers such as Botox, which work on expression wrinkles, are ineffective for sleep wrinkles.

item.title: What do British people call cigarettes?
item.description: FAG, a brand of the Schaeffler Group. Cigarette, in British slang. Fagging, in British public schools. What is cigarette called in Britain?
